title: What Every Christian Needs to Understand About Israel
description:
Whatâ€™s really going on with Israel and why should Christians care?

title: How God called this former cop to become a full-time content creator - with Ryan Tillman
description:
In this inspiring episode of Directed Life, we sit down with Ryan Tillman, the founder of Breaking Barriers United. Ryan shares his unique journey of transitioning from a career in law enforcement to becoming a full-time content creator. He discusses the challenges he faced, the fears he overcame, and the faith that guided him through it all.

Ryan emphasizes the importance of saying yes to God, even when His blessings and provisions come from unexpected places. He encourages us to walk by faith, even when it's uncomfortable, and to move even when we can't see the path ahead.

This episode also explores the idea of bridging the gap between law enforcement and civilians, and how we can help each other as the body of Christ. Ryan passionately talks about using our God-given talents and how ministry is not bound by the four walls of a church building.
Join us as we delve into these topics and more, learning from Ryan's experiences and gaining insights on how to live a directed life.

Don't forget to like, comment, and subscribe to our channel for more inspiring episodes. Share this video with your friends and followers to spread the message. For more details and resources, check out the link in the description. Stay tuned for our next episode, and remember, God is the director and you are the directed!

#DirectedLife #BreakingBarriersUnited #FaithJourney #WalkByFaith #TrustInGod #OutOfTheBox #UseYourTalents #BeyondWalls

How to give your business back to God? | DL
description:
Some people would argue that boldly declaring and owning your love for Jesus in your business is going to alienate you from people in the marketplace.

Settling in to pursuing kingdom first entities will look different for every business owner, but the truth is that God is so much bigger than our perception of the marketplace.

No matter what sect your business serves, remember this: All people need to see the kingdom of heaven, regardless of where they stand with their faith. 

When it comes to business operation, the way in which you conduct your company should always be in alignment with the values that reflect the fruit of the Spirit.

For more information on how to give your business back to God, check out the newest episode of â€œDirected Lifeâ€.

title: God says, "Take care of My story...â€ | DL
description:
As Believers, we know that the most powerful things in our arsenal are our testimoniesâ€”our stories.

The Bible, after all, is told in the form of hundreds of smaller stories tying in to one big story of redemption through Jesus and reconciliation with the Father.

God wants you to take care of His storyâ€¦so what does that look like?

In your business and in your decision-making, remember that Godâ€™s love and Godâ€™s story needs to be taken care of, and do your best to honor that as you move forward in your business.

For more information on kingdom entrepreneurship and partnering with the Lord in your business, check out the full episode of â€œDirected Lifeâ€.

title: Put God's house FIRST! | DL
description:
Part of the pitfall of being a creative entrepreneurs is that you never run out of ideas!

Now, thatâ€™s a pretty good problem to have, especially when the world struggles with coming up with creative solutions, but it doesnâ€™t come without struggle.

You may have an awesome idea for a business, and perhaps your idea is so good that it could serve multiple sects of people. 

If thatâ€™s the case, remember this: God says HIS HOUSE FIRST!

Donâ€™t get so caught up in conquering the world that you forget that God first priority is His bride.

title: Surrender your business to the Holy Spirit | DL
description:
As kingdom entrepreneurs, oftentimes thereâ€™s a tension between our business and our faith.

If youâ€™ve experienced this tension, you know that a deep pressure can ensue when itâ€™s time for decision-making regarding the practicals of your business.

It may seem like all the pressure is on you to make the right decisionâ€¦think again!

The Lord is faithful to guide you, even in the moments where you are at a loss of what to do. Owner and founder of Divine Persuasion Studio, Wendell McKinney recalls his life as always being in the hands of the Lord, even in moments where it looked like he was his own captain.

If youâ€™ve been feeling the weight of decision-making in your business on your shoulders, check out the latest episode of Directed Life for an encouraging message.

title: How God EXPLODED a creative technology company to serve the church - with Wendell McKinney
description:
As a believer, there is a temptation to separate your business and you faithâ€”after all, business is business and your faith is your faith, right?Wrong! Living a Directed Life means that all elements of your life are submitted to the direction and instruction of the Holy Spirit.To put it simplyâ€”your business and you faith are not meant to be separate.

As Kingdom Entrepreneurs, one thing weâ€™ve learned is thisâ€”when you honor Godâ€™s ways in the framework of your business, you sit underneath an open heaven where abundant blessings flow freely.In this episode of â€œDirected Lifeâ€, host Kap Chatfield sits down with founder and owner of Divine Persuasion Studio, Wendell McKinney. Together they discuss ministry in the marketplace and the blessing that ensues when you use you business to serve the church. If youâ€™ve been hesitant to lean into your faith in you business endeavors, check out this new episode for some divine perspective.

title: How to forgive yourself and move on (YOU CAN'T)
description:
Do you want to know how to forgive yourself from past mistakes? Is it possible to forgive yourself? Do you ask yourself "how can I forgive myself"?
 
You can't, and it's not.

Nowhere in the Bible does it say that you can forgive yourself.

And that's actually a good thing.

You see, we can't forgive ourselves because we don't OWE an account to ourselves.

We owe an account to the God who created us in His image.

And, thankfully, He provided a way through the sacrifice of His son on the cross to pay for our sin in full.

In other words...

To cancel our debt!

So don't try harder to forgive yourself. It'll get you nowhere.

Instead, seek God, ask HIM for His forgiveness through Jesus, and freely receive the forgiveness that He paid a high price to give to you.
